Supreme Court — Appellate Term, October, 1899.

Before Freedman, P. J., MacLean and Leventritt, JJ.

Egbert B. Seaman, Appellant, v. Sophie Fleischman, Respondent.— Appeal by the plaintiff from a judgment rendered In favor of the defendant in the Municipal Court, tenth district, borough of Manhattan. Hugo S. Mack, for Appellant: Shipman, Larocque & Choate, for Respondent.

Judgment affirmed, with costs. No opinion.
